README.md:====
README.md:
README.md:Javaで構築したオープンソースグループウェアです。パソコン、携帯電話、スマートフォンなど幅広い端末に対応しています。
README.md:
README.md:関連情報

jetspeed/src/main/resources/org/apache/jetspeed/services/db/repository.dtd:	This DTD describes the grammar of the Descriptor repository

jetspeed/src/main/resources/org/apache/jetspeed/services/db/repository.dtd:<!ELEMENT JdbcConnectionDescriptor (dbms.name, jdbc.level?, ((driver.name, url.protocol, url.subprotocol, url.dbalias) | datasource.name), user.name?, user.passwd?)>
jetspeed/src/main/resources/org/apache/jetspeed/services/db/repository.dtd:<!ELEMENT ClassDescriptor (ExtentDescriptor|(JdbcConnectionDescriptor?,  class.name, class.proxy?, class.extent*, schema.name?, table.name, orderby?, conversionStrategy?, rowReader?, FieldDescriptor+, ReferenceDescriptor*, CollectionDescriptor*))>
jetspeed/src/main/resources/org/apache/jetspeed/services/db/repository.dtd:<!ELEMENT FieldDescriptor (field.name, column.name, jdbc_type, PrimaryKey?, autoincrement?, locking?)>
jetspeed/src/main/resources/org/apache/jetspeed/services/db/repository.dtd:<!ELEMENT ReferenceDescriptor (rdfield.name, referenced.class, fk_descriptor_ids, auto.retrieve?, auto.update?, auto.delete?, refreshReference? )>
jetspeed/src/main/resources/org/apache/jetspeed/services/db/repository.dtd:<!ELEMENT CollectionDescriptor (cdfield.name, items.class, inverse_fk_descriptor_ids, collection.class?, proxy?, auto.retrieve?, auto.update?, auto.delete?, indirection_table?, fks_pointing_to_this_class?, fks_pointing_to_items_class?, orderby?, refreshCollection?)>

sql/postgres/5120.sql:-- AIPO_LICENSE
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:CREATE TABLE AIPO_LICENSE
sql/postgres/5120.sql:(
sql/postgres/5120.sql:   LICENSE_ID serial,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:   LICENSE VARCHAR (99) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:   LIMIT_USERS INTEGER,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:   PRIMARY KEY(LICENSE_ID)
sql/postgres/5120.sql:);
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-- TURBINE_PERMISSION
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:CREATE TABLE TURBINE_PERMISSION
sql/postgres/5120.sql:(
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PERMISSION_ID serial,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PERMISSION_NAME VARCHAR (99) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    OBJECTDATA bytea,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PRIMARY KEY(PERMISSION_ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    UNIQUE (PERMISSION_NAME)
sql/postgres/5120.sql:);
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-- TURBINE_ROLE
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:CREATE TABLE TURBINE_ROLE
sql/postgres/5120.sql:(
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    ROLE_ID serial,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    ROLE_NAME VARCHAR (99) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    OBJECTDATA bytea,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PRIMARY KEY(ROLE_ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    UNIQUE (ROLE_NAME)
sql/postgres/5120.sql:);
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-- TURBINE_GROUP
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:CREATE TABLE TURBINE_GROUP
sql/postgres/5120.sql:(
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    GROUP_ID serial,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    GROUP_NAME VARCHAR (99) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    OBJECTDATA bytea,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    OWNER_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    GROUP_ALIAS_NAME VARCHAR (99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PUBLIC_FLAG CHAR,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PRIMARY KEY(GROUP_ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    UNIQUE (GROUP_NAME),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    UNIQUE (OWNER_ID, GROUP_ALIAS_NAME)
sql/postgres/5120.sql:);
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-- TURBINE_ROLE_PERMISSION
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:CREATE TABLE TURBINE_ROLE_PERMISSION
sql/postgres/5120.sql:(
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    ROLE_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PERMISSION_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PRIMARY KEY(ROLE_ID,PERMISSION_ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    FOREIGN KEY (ROLE_ID) REFERENCES TURBINE_ROLE (ROLE_ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    FOREIGN KEY (PERMISSION_ID) REFERENCES TURBINE_PERMISSION (PERMISSION_ID)
sql/postgres/5120.sql:);
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:CREATE UNIQUE INDEX ROLE_PERMISSION_INDEX
sql/postgres/5120.sql:  ON TURBINE_ROLE_PERMISSION(ROLE_ID,PERMISSION_ID);
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-- TURBINE_USER
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:CREATE TABLE TURBINE_USER
sql/postgres/5120.sql:(
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    USER_ID serial,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    LOGIN_NAME VARCHAR (32) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PASSWORD_VALUE VARCHAR (200) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    FIRST_NAME VARCHAR (99) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    LAST_NAME VARCHAR (99) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    EMAIL VARCHAR (99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    CONFIRM_VALUE VARCHAR (99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    MODIFIED TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    CREATED TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    LAST_LOGIN TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    DISABLED CHAR,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    OBJECTDATA bytea,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PASSWORD_CHANGED TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    COMPANY_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    POSITION_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    IN_TELEPHONE VARCHAR (15),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    OUT_TELEPHONE VARCHAR (15),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    CELLULAR_PHONE VARCHAR (15),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    CELLULAR_MAIL VARCHAR (99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    CELLULAR_UID VARCHAR (99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    FIRST_NAME_KANA VARCHAR (99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    LAST_NAME_KANA VARCHAR(99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PHOTO bytea,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    CREATED_USER_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    UPDATED_USER_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PRIMARY KEY(USER_ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    UNIQUE (LOGIN_NAME)
sql/postgres/5120.sql:);
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-- TURBINE_USER_GROUP_ROLE
sql/postgres/5120.sql:-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
sql/postgres/5120.sql:
sql/postgres/5120.sql:CREATE TABLE TURBINE_USER_GROUP_ROLE
sql/postgres/5120.sql:(
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    ID serial,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    USER_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    GROUP_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    ROLE_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PRIMARY KEY(ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    FOREIGN KEY (USER_ID) REFERENCES TURBINE_USER (USER_ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    FOREIGN KEY (GROUP_ID) REFERENCES TURBINE_GROUP (GROUP_ID),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    FOREIGN KEY (ROLE_ID) REFERENCES TURBINE_ROLE (ROLE_ID)
sql/postgres/5120.sql:);

sql/postgres/5120.sql:(

sql/postgres/5120.sql:    OWNER_ID INTEGER,

sql/postgres/5120.sql:    END_DATE TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    NAME VARCHAR (99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PLACE VARCHAR (99),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    NOTE VARCHAR,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PUBLIC_FLAG VARCHAR (1),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    EDIT_FLAG VARCHAR (1),
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    CREATE_USER_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    UPDATE_USER_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    CREATE_DATE DATE,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    UPDATE_DATE TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/5120.sql:    PRIMARY KEY(SCHEDULE_ID)
sql/postgres/5120.sql:);

sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    WIKI_NAME VARCHAR (64) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    PARENT_ID INTEGER DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    NOTE TEXT,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    CREATE_USER_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    UPDATE_USER_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    CREATE_DATE DATE,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    UPDATE_DATE TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    PRIMARY KEY(WIKI_ID)
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:);
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:

sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:CREATE TABLE EIP_T_WIKI_FILE
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:(
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    FILE_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    OWNER_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    WIKI_ID INTEGER,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    FILE_NAME VARCHAR (128) NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    FILE_PATH TEXT NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    FILE_THUMBNAIL bytea,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    CREATE_DATE DATE,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    UPDATE_DATE TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    FOREIGN KEY (WIKI_ID) REFERENCES EIP_T_WIKI (WIKI_ID) ON DELETE CASCADE,
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    PRIMARY KEY (FILE_ID)
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:);
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:

sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , EXPLANATION        TEXT                                       --説明
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , ADMIN_USER_ID      INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --管理者
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PROGRESS_FLG       CHARACTER VARYING(1)           NOT NULL    --進捗率入力フラグ 1:進捗率を入力する 0:タスクを元に自動計算する
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PROGRESS_RATE      INTEGER                                    --進捗率
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , CREATE_USER_ID     INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --登録ユーザーID
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , UPDATE_USER_ID     INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --更新ユーザーID
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , CREATE_DATE        TIMESTAMP                                                          --登録日
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , UPDATE_DATE        TIMESTAMP                                                          --更新日
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PRIMARY KEY (PROJECT_ID)
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:);

sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:      TASK_ID                INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --タスクID
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PARENT_TASK_ID         INTEGER                                    --親タスクID
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PROJECT_ID             INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --プロジェクトID
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , TRACKER                TEXT                           NOT NULL    --トラッカー 1:機能 2:バグ 3:サポート
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , TASK_NAME              TEXT                           NOT NULL    --タスク名
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , EXPLANATION            TEXT                                       --説明
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , STATUS                 TEXT                           NOT NULL    --ステータス 1:新規 2:進行中 3:解決 4:フィードバック 5:終了 6:却下
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PRIORITY               TEXT                           NOT NULL    --優先度 1:高 2:中 3:低
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , START_PLAN_DATE        DATE                                       --開始予定日
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , END_PLAN_DATE          DATE                                       --完了予定日
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , START_DATE             DATE                                       --開始実績日
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , END_DATE               DATE                                       --完了実績日
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PLAN_WORKLOAD          DECIMAL(8,3)                               --計画工数（時間）
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PROGRESS_RATE          INTEGER                                    --進捗率
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , ORDER_NO               INTEGER                                    --表示順
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , CREATE_USER_ID         INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --登録ユーザーID
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , UPDATE_USER_ID         INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --更新ユーザーID
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , CREATE_DATE            TIMESTAMP                                                          --登録日
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , UPDATE_DATE            TIMESTAMP                                                          --更新日
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:    , PRIMARY KEY (TASK_ID)
sql/postgres/7020to8000.sql:);

sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , ADMIN_USER_ID      INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --管理者
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PROGRESS_FLG       CHARACTER VARYING(1)           NOT NULL    --進捗率入力フラグ 1:進捗率を入力する 0:タスクを元に自動計算する
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PROGRESS_RATE      INTEGER                                    --進捗率
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , CREATE_USER_ID     INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --登録ユーザーID
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , UPDATE_USER_ID     INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --更新ユーザーID
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , CREATE_DATE        TIMESTAMP                                                          --登録日
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , UPDATE_DATE        TIMESTAMP                                                          --更新日
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PRIMARY KEY (PROJECT_ID)
sql/postgres/org001.sql:);

sql/postgres/org001.sql:CREATE TABLE EIP_T_PROJECT_TASK (
sql/postgres/org001.sql:      TASK_ID                INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --タスクID
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PARENT_TASK_ID         INTEGER                                    --親タスクID
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PROJECT_ID             INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --プロジェクトID
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , TRACKER                TEXT                           NOT NULL    --トラッカー 1:機能 2:バグ 3:サポート
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , TASK_NAME              TEXT                           NOT NULL    --タスク名
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , EXPLANATION            TEXT                                       --説明
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , STATUS                 TEXT                           NOT NULL    --ステータス 1:新規 2:進行中 3:解決 4:フィードバック 5:終了 6:却下
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PRIORITY               TEXT                           NOT NULL    --優先度 1:高 2:中 3:低
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , START_PLAN_DATE        DATE                                       --開始予定日
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , END_PLAN_DATE          DATE                                       --完了予定日
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , START_DATE             DATE                                       --開始実績日
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , END_DATE               DATE                                       --完了実績日
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PLAN_WORKLOAD          DECIMAL(8,3)                               --計画工数（時間）
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PROGRESS_RATE          INTEGER                                    --進捗率
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , ORDER_NO               INTEGER                                    --表示順
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , CREATE_USER_ID         INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --登録ユーザーID
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , UPDATE_USER_ID         INTEGER                        NOT NULL    --更新ユーザーID
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , CREATE_DATE            TIMESTAMP                                                          --登録日
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , UPDATE_DATE            TIMESTAMP                                                          --更新日
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    , PRIMARY KEY (TASK_ID)
sql/postgres/org001.sql:);
sql/postgres/org001.sql:
sql/postgres/org001.sql:CREATE INDEX eip_t_project_task_project_id_index ON EIP_T_PROJECT_TASK (PROJECT_ID);

sql/postgres/org001.sql:    LAST_MESSAGE TEXT,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    LAST_UPDATE_DATE TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NULL,

sql/postgres/org001.sql:    PHOTO bytea,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    PHOTO_SMARTPHONE bytea,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    PHOTO_MODIFIED TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    HAS_PHOTO VARCHAR (1) DEFAULT 'F',
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    CREATE_DATE TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    UPDATE_DATE TIMESTAMP,

sql/postgres/org001.sql:(
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    MESSAGE_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    ROOM_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    USER_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,

sql/postgres/org001.sql:    MEMBER_COUNT INTEGER NOT NULL,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    CREATE_DATE TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    UPDATE_DATE TIMESTAMP,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    FOREIGN KEY (ROOM_ID) REFERENCES EIP_T_MESSAGE_ROOM (ROOM_ID) ON DELETE CASCADE,
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    PRIMARY KEY (MESSAGE_ID)
sql/postgres/org001.sql:);
sql/postgres/org001.sql:

sql/postgres/org001.sql:(

sql/postgres/org001.sql:    ROOM_ID INTEGER NOT NULL,

sql/postgres/org001.sql:    IS_READ VARCHAR(1) DEFAULT 'F',
sql/postgres/org001.sql:    FOREIGN KEY (MESSAGE_ID) REFERENCES EIP_T_MESSAGE (MESSAGE_ID) ON DELETE CASCADE,

sql/postgres/org001.sql:);

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# This is used by the SecurityService to make the password checking
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# secure. When enabled, passwords are transformed by a one-way
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# function into a sequence of bytes that is base64 encoded.
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# It is impossible to guess the plain-text form of the password
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# from the representation. When user logs in, the entered password
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# is transformed the same way and then compared with stored value.
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Default: false
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.secure.passwords=false
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# This property lets you choose what digest algorithm will be used
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# for encrypting passwords. Check documentation of your JRE for
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# available algorithms.
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Default: SHA
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.secure.passwords.algorithm=SHA
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Role(s) to assign to new user.  Multiple Role must be comma separated.
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.newuser.roles=user
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Default permission(s) when object have no permissions defined
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# The follow permissions are define in the default Jetspeed installation:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#     view, customize, minimize, maximize, close
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#     * = All permissions
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.permission.default.anonymous=view
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.permission.default.loggedin=*
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# During logon, username and password can be case sensitive or case insensitive
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# This option configures the logon username and password to be case sensitive or insensitive
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# if its case insensitive, then "logon.casesensitive.upper" controls whether the username and
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# password or converted to upper or lower case before passing on to the database
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.caseinsensitive.username=false
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.caseinsensitive.password=false
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.caseinsensitive.upper=true
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Auto-Account-Disable Feature
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.logon.auto.disable=false
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# 3 logon strikes per 300 seconds and your out
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.logon.strike.count=3
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.logon.strike.interval=300
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# dont allow more than 10 over any time period
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.logon.strike.max=10
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# anonymous user
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.user.anonymous=anon
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Caching
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.caching.enable=true
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Number of days until password expires. To disable
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# this feature, set it to 0.
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Default:  0
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:services.JetspeedSecurity.password.expiration.period=0
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Comma separated list of system users. System users cannot 
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# be deleted because they are essential to security service.
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:#
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/conf/JetspeedSecurity.template:# Default: admin, anon

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:      <xsl:if test="$showtitle = 'true' and $description">

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:      </xsl:if></p>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:      </card>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:  </xsl:template>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    </xsl:if></p>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:  </xsl:template>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    </xsl:if></p>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    <xsl:call-template name="dollar-cleaner">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:      <xsl:with-param name="chars">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:        <xsl:value-of select="."/>            
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:        </xsl:with-param>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:      </xsl:call-template>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:  </xsl:template>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:  <xsl:template name="dollar-cleaner">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    <xsl:param name="chars"></xsl:param>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    <xsl:choose>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    <xsl:when test="contains($chars,'$') and 
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:                    not(starts-with(substring-after($chars,'$'), '$'))" >
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:      <xsl:value-of select="substring-before($chars,'$')"
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:            />$$<xsl:call-template
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:                  name="dollar-cleaner">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:                  <xsl:with-param name="chars">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:                    <xsl:value-of select="substring-after($chars,'$')" />
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:                  </xsl:with-param>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:                </xsl:call-template>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    </xsl:when>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    <xsl:otherwise><xsl:value-of select="$chars" /></xsl:otherwise>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    </xsl:choose> 
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:  </xsl:template>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:    
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss-wml.xsl:</xsl:stylesheet>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:                xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:                xmlns:downlevel="http://my.netscape.com/rdf/simple/0.9/"
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:                exclude-result-prefixes="downlevel rdf"
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:                version="1.0">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:     <xsl:output indent="yes" 
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:                 method="html"
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:                 omit-xml-declaration="yes"/>                
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:param name="itemdisplayed" select="number(15)"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:param name="openinpopup" select="'false'"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:param name="showdescription" select="'true'"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:param name="showtitle" select="'true'"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:param name="showtextinput" select="'true'"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:template match="/rss">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <div>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <xsl:apply-templates select="channel"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </div>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    </xsl:template>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:template match="/rdf:RDF">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <div>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <xsl:apply-templates select="downlevel:channel"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </div>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    </xsl:template>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:template match="channel">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <xsl:variable name="description" select="description"/>    
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <xsl:if test="$showtitle = 'true' and $description">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <p>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:          <xsl:apply-templates select="image|../image" mode="channel"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:          <xsl:value-of select="$description"/>            
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        </p>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </xsl:if>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <ul>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <xsl:apply-templates select="item[$itemdisplayed&gt;=position()]"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </ul>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <xsl:if test="$showtextinput = 'true'">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <xsl:apply-templates select="textinput"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </xsl:if>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    </xsl:template>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    <xsl:template match="downlevel:channel">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <xsl:variable name="description" select="downlevel:description"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <xsl:if test="$showtitle = 'true' and $description">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <p>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <xsl:choose>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:         <xsl:when test="count(../downlevel:image)">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:          <xsl:apply-templates select="../downlevel:image" mode="channel"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:          <xsl:value-of select="$description"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:         </xsl:when>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:         <xsl:otherwise>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:          <a>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:           <xsl:attribute name="href"><xsl:value-of select="downlevel:link"/></xsl:attribute>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:           <xsl:if test="$openinpopup = 'true'">
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:            <xsl:attribute name="target">_blank</xsl:attribute>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:           </xsl:if>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:           <xsl:value-of select="$description"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:          </a>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:         </xsl:otherwise>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        </xsl:choose>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        </p>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </xsl:if>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </ul>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      <xsl:if test="$showtextinput = 'true'">

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </xsl:if>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        </xsl:if>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </li>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:    </xsl:template>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <a>

war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:        <input type="submit" name="submit" value="{title}"/>
war/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/xsl/rss.xsl:      </form>

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			again is there anyone who loves or pursues or desires to obtain
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			pain of itself, because it is pain, but because occasionally
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			circumstances occur in which toil and pain can procure him some
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			great pleasure. To take a trivial example, which of us ever
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			undertakes laborious physical exercise, except to obtain some
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			advantage from it? But who has any right to find fault with a man
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			who chooses to enjoy a pleasure that has no annoying consequences,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			or one who avoids a pain that produces no resultant pleasure?" 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:			</p>
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/bench/widget_construction_test.php:		<? }

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Changes from Dojo 0.4 dojo.widgets to new dijit project
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:=======================================================
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:The widgets and widget infrastructure have been separated into separate project,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:vastly streamlined and with a new directory structure.   There are many other changes.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Markup
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:dojoType="button" replaced by dojoType="dijit.Button"  Must use fully qualified class name,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:and it's case-sensitive.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Need to manually dojo.require("dojo.parser") to get parsing
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Widget namespaces and widget auto-loading are desupported.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:onClick="foo" now overrides (ie, replaces) the default onClick() function rather than attaching to it,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:so widget designers should make empty onClick() functions (when appropriate).
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Programmatic creation
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:---------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Create widgets via
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:	new dijit.Button(params, srcNodeRef)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:createWidget() call removed since multiple renderers are no longer supported (see next section).
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:At least for the dijit widgets, all widgets are guaranteed to work programmatically, which in
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:effect means that all widgets must have templates, unless the default <div> works.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Renderers
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:---------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Removed support for multiple renderers (svg & vml & a11y) for a single widget.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:If a widget wants to render differently on different platforms, there must be
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:branching code inside the widget, or it needs to call a library that branches
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:based on the browser type (like dojo.gfx or dojo.charting).
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Templates
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:---------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:"this." is no longer used within ${} substitution notation.  See ticket #2905.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:dojoRoot,buildScriptBase,dojoModuleUrl are no longer supported, but
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:any JavaScript properties on the widget's 'this' may be referenced with dotted notation.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:The attributes dojoOn* are desupported (including dojoOnBuild);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:also can't use id attribute to affect a dojoAttachPoint.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:dojoAttachEvent is case sensitive, so capitalization matters.   You will probably have
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:to change
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:dojoAttachEvent="onClick"
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:to
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:dojoAttachEvent="onclick: onClick"
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:(given that the event name is lowercase, and assuming that the method name is camel case)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:lists within dojoAttachPoint, dojoAttachEvent, waiRole, and waiState are now comma-separated
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:(not separated by semi-colons)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Standard HTML attributes like 'id', 'name', 'lang', etc. are carried over programmatically
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:by the _Widget constructor and do not need to be declared in the template (see _Widget.attributeMap)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Parent/Child relationships
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:--------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:By default widgets exist as islands, not knowing about their parent widget or children widgets.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:The exception is the destroy() function which will also delete all descendant widgets.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Some widgets like Tree and SplitContainer will know about their children, but those widgets
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:will use the special mixins in Container.js / Layout.js. 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:Widget.js base class
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:--------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: - Widget.js, Domwidget.js, HtmlWidget.js combined into dijit.base.Widget, with TemplatedWidget mixin
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:for widgets with templates
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: - on widget creation, postMixInProperties(), buildRendering() and postCreate() is called.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: fillInTemplate() is no longer called.  In addition, those functions call signatures have changed.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: No arguments are passed.  To get the source dom Node, just reference this.srcDomNode.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:When postCreate() is called the widget children don't yet exist.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: - The TemplatedWidget mixin defines buildRendering().  widgetsInTemplate not ported yet.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: - onResized() removed
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: - the whole parent/child relationship thing is gone
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: - extraArgs[] is gone
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: - postCreate() called but child widgets don't exist yet
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: - templateCssPath ignored.   User must manually include tundra.css file
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/changes.txt: 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/themes/a11y/README.txt:This folder contains images used by all themes when in "high-contrast" mode.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dijit/themes/a11y/README.txt:

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:All files within this directory were derived from the Common Locale
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:Data Repository (see http://unicode.org/cldr)  The CLDR project is
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:responsible for the accuracy and maintenance of this data.  A copy
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:of this data is checked into the Dojo util project as a zip file.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:The XML data is transformed to the JSON-style Javascript you see
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:under the nls/ directory.  These Javascript files include data
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:necessary to do things like format and parse dates, numbers, and
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:currencies in different locales to consider cultural differences.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:They are used by other modules in core Dojo such as dojo.date,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:dojo.number and dojo.currency.  It usually is not necessary to use
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:dojo.cldr directly.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:An arbitrary subset of locales have been checked in to dojo/cldr
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:under svn.  To support other locales, the full set may be generated
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:by using xslt scripts in the util/buildscripts/cldr/ ant script.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:Hundreds of locales are supported by the CLDR project.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojo/cldr/README:See terms of use: http://www.unicode.org/copyright.html#Exhibit1

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:Project description
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:Low-latency data transfer from servers to clients. dojox.cometd implements a
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:Bayeux protocol client for use with most Bayeux servers. See cometd.com for
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:details on Cometd or on the Bayeux protocol.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:Needs a cooperating Bayeux server

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:Documentation
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:See http://cometd.com
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:Installation instructions
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/_cometd/README:Use this library with (preferably through) an existing Cometd server.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:This directory contains a set of themes for the DojoX Charting 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:engine that are based on the visual stylings of the PlotKit
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:chart kit, created by Alastair Tse:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:http://www.liquidx.net/plotkit/
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:...whose work we admire.  Consider these themes to not be a 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:ripoff of his fine work, but instead a true homage: his charts
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:are beautiful, and we stand in awe.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/charting/themes/PlotKit/README:--trt, 2007-06-08
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:DojoX Collections
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:Version 0.9
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:Release date: 05/27/2007
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:Project state: stable
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:Project authors
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:	Tom Trenka (ttrenka@gmail.com)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:Project description
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:DojoX Collections is the port of the original Dojo 0.4.x collection classes.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:It is intended for use by people who are looking for a little bit more 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:functionality out of common collections, like ArrayLists or Dictionaries.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:Included are the Iterator and DictionaryIterator classes, both of which can
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:operate on standard arrays and objects (respectively).
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:Dependencies:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/collections/README:DojoX Collections has no dependencies, outside of Dojo Core.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/color/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/color/README:Both a port of the older dojo.gfx.color work (Cal Henderson) as well as some
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/color/README:new additions (Generator, Tom Trenka).  Everything is applied to an alias of
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/color/README:dojo.Color or dojo.color, so that you can just use dojox.color.Color instead
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/color/README:with extended methods.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:DojoX Cryptography
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:Version 0.9
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:Release date: 05/27/2007
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:Project state: beta
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:Project authors
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:	Tom Trenka (ttrenka@gmail.com)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:Project description
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:The DojoX Cryptography project is a set of implementations of public crypto
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:algorithms.  At the time of writing, only MD5 and Blowfish are complete; others
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:will follow.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:DojoX Cryptography is comprised of both symmetric (Blowfish) and asymmetric
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:(MD5) algorithms.  Symmetric algs always implement encrypt() and decrypt()
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:methods; asymmetric algs implement compute().
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:Dependencies:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:DojoX Cryptography has no dependencies, outside of the Dojo package system 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:and DOH.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:Installation instructions
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:Grab the following from the Dojo SVN Repository:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:http://svn.dojotoolkit.org/var/src/dojo/dojox/trunk/crypto.js
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:http://svn.dojotoolkit.org/var/src/dojo/dojox/trunk/crypto/*

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/crypto/README:...which should be at the same level as your Dojo checkout.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/data/README:The DojoX Data project is a container for extensions and extra example stores
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/data/README:that implement the dojo.data APIs.  It may also contain utility functions for
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/data/README:working with specific types of data.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/data/README:	documents.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/data/README:	matching.  Similar to the 0.4.X ComboBox dataUrl parameter.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:DojoX Django Template Language
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Version 0.0
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Release date: 09/20/2007
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Project state: experimental/feature incomplete
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Project authors
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:	Neil Roberts (pottedmeat@dojotoolkit.org)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Project description
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:The Django Template language uses a system of templates that can be compiled
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:once and rendered indefinitely afterwards. It uses a simple system of tags
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:and filters.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:This aims to be a 1:1 match with the Django Template Language as outlined in
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:http://www.djangoproject.com/documentation/templates/. Many common tags and
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:filters have been implemented (see below), along with new filters and tags as
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:necessary (see below).
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:The Django Template Language is intended within Django to only handle text.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Our implementation is able to handle HTML in addition to text. Actually, the
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:text and HTML portions of dojox.dtl are two separate layers, the HTML layer
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:sits on top of the text layer (base). It's also been implemented in such a way
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:that you have little to fear when moving your code from Django to dojox.dtl.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Your existing templates should work, and will benefit from the massive
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:performance gain of being able to manipulate nodes, rather than having to do
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:clunky innerHTML swaps you would have to do with a text-only system. It also
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:allows for new HTML-centric abilities, outlined below.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Despite having two levels of complexity, if you write your tags correctly, they
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:will work in both environments.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Dependencies
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Base:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:dojox.string.Builder
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Date filters and tags:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:dojox.date.php
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Widget:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:dijit._Widget
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:dijit._Container
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Installation instructions
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Grab the following from the Dojo SVN Repository:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:http://svn.dojotoolkit.org/var/src/dojo/dojox/trunk/dtl.js
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:http://svn.dojotoolkit.org/var/src/dojo/dojox/trunk/dtl/*
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Install into the following directory structure:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:/dojox/dtl/
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:...which should be at the same level as your Dojo checkout.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:What's Been Done
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:| Implemented |     Tag     | Text Unit Test | HTML Unit Test |
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:|      X      | block       |       X        |                |
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:|      X      | comment     |       X        |                |
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:|      X      | cycle       |       X        |                |
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:|      X      | debug       |       X        |                |
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:|      X      | extends     |       X        |                |
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:|      X      | filter      |       X        |                |

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:HTML-Specific Additions
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:{%extends "shared:templates/template.html" %}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:When using the {% extends %} tag, we don't always want to replace the parent
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:node in DOM. For example, if we have a list view and a detail view, but both
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:share the same base template, we want it to share the parent template. This
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:basically means that the same nodes will be used in the parent for both views.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:To use this, simply add "shared:" to the beginning of the specified template.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:<!--{% commented markup %}-->
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Some browsers treat comment nodes as full fledged nodes. If performance is
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:important to you, you can wrap your markup in comments. The comments will be
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:automatically stripped for browsers that cannot support this.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Attribute Tags
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:If a tag name begins with "attr:" then it will be able to inject an object
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:into the parsed template. (See dojox.dtl.tag.event.EventNode)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:onclick/onmouseover/etc attributes work by attaching to the rendering object.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:tstyle attribute allows for styles to be changed dynamically. Use them just
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:like a "style" attribute.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:attach attribute attaches the node to the rendering object.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:New Context Functions
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:setThis() and getThis() returns the object "in charge" of the current rendering.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:This is used so that we can attach events.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:mixin() and filter() clone the current context, and either add to or reduce
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:the keys in the context.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Buffers
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Both the base and HTML versions of dojox.dtl use buffers. The base version uses
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:dojox.string.Builder and the HTML version uses dojox.dtl.HtmlBuffer.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:The HTML buffer has several calls important to rendering:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:setParent/getParent/concat/remove:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:setParent and concat are used in order to render our HTML. As we move through
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:the parsed template, different nodes change the parent or add on to the
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:current parent. getParent is useful in things like the attribute tags, since
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:they can use getParent to find the node that they're an attribute on. remove is
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:used during unrendering.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:setAttribute:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Sets an attribute on the current parent
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Tags Need clone/unrender Functions.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:One of the biggest challenges of getting dojox.dtl to work in an HTML
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:environment was logic blocks. Nodes and objects inside a for loop need to be
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:cloned, they can't simply be re-rendered, especially if they involve a Node.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:Also, in the case of an if/else block, we need to be able to not just render
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:one of the blocks, but also unrender the second.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/dtl/README:This is really simple code, a good example is the dojox.dtl.HtmlNode

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:/** 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		An implementation of Flash 8's ExternalInterface that works with Flash 6
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		and which is source-compatible with Flash 8. 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		@author Brad Neuberg, bkn3@columbia.edu 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:*/
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:class DojoExternalInterface{
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static var available:Boolean;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static var dojoPath = "";
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static var _fscommandReady = false;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static var _callbacks = new Array();
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static function initialize(){ 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		//getURL("javascript:console.debug('FLASH:DojoExternalInterface initialize')");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// FIXME: Set available variable by testing for capabilities
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		DojoExternalInterface.available = true;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// extract the dojo base path
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		DojoExternalInterface.dojoPath = DojoExternalInterface.getDojoPath();
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		//getURL("javascript:console.debug('FLASH:dojoPath="+DojoExternalInterface.dojoPath+"')");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// Sometimes, on IE, the fscommand infrastructure can take a few hundred
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// milliseconds the first time a page loads. Set a timer to keep checking
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// to make sure we can issue fscommands; otherwise, our calls to fscommand
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// for setCallback() and loaded() will just "disappear"
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		_root.fscommandReady = false;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var fsChecker = function(){
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:			// issue a test fscommand
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:			fscommand("fscommandReady");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:			
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:			// JavaScript should set _root.fscommandReady if it got the call
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:			if(_root.fscommandReady == "true"){
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:				DojoExternalInterface._fscommandReady = true;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:				clearInterval(_root.fsTimer);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:			}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		};
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		_root.fsTimer = setInterval(fsChecker, 100);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static function addCallback(methodName:String, instance:Object, 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:											method:Function) : Boolean{
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// A variable that indicates whether the call below succeeded
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		_root._succeeded = null;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// Callbacks are registered with the JavaScript side as follows.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// On the Flash side, we maintain a lookup table that associates
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// the methodName with the actual instance and method that are
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// associated with this method.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// Using fscommand, we send over the action "addCallback", with the
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// argument being the methodName to add, such as "foobar".
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// The JavaScript takes these values and registers the existence of
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// this callback point.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// precede the method name with a _ character in case it starts

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		_callbacks[_callbacks.length] = methodName;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// The API for ExternalInterface says we have to make sure the call

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// get our parameters

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		for(var i = 0; i < numArgs; i++){

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// get our function name
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var functionName = _root._functionName;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// now get the actual instance and method object to execute on,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// using our lookup table that was constructed by calls to
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// addCallback on initialization

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var method = _callbacks["_" + functionName]._method;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// execute it
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var results = method.apply(instance, jsArgs);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// return the results
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		_root._returnResult = results;

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var url = _root._url;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var start = url.indexOf("baseRelativePath=") + "baseRelativePath=".length;

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:		return path;

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash6/DojoExternalInterface.as:// vim:ts=4:noet:tw=0:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:/**
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	A wrapper around Flash 8's ExternalInterface; DojoExternalInterface is needed so that we
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	can do a Flash 6 implementation of ExternalInterface, and be able
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	to support having a single codebase that uses DojoExternalInterface
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	across Flash versions rather than having two seperate source bases,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	where one uses ExternalInterface and the other uses DojoExternalInterface.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	DojoExternalInterface class does a variety of optimizations to bypass ExternalInterface's
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	unbelievably bad performance so that we can have good performance
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	on Safari; see the blog post
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	http://codinginparadise.org/weblog/2006/02/how-to-speed-up-flash-8s.html
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	for details.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	@author Brad Neuberg, bkn3@columbia.edu
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:*/
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:import flash.external.ExternalInterface;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:class DojoExternalInterface{
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static var available:Boolean;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static var dojoPath = "";
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static function initialize(){
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// extract the dojo base path
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		DojoExternalInterface.dojoPath = DojoExternalInterface.getDojoPath();
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// see if we need to do an express install
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var install:ExpressInstall = new ExpressInstall();
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		if(install.needsUpdate){
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:			install.init();
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// register our callback functions
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		ExternalInterface.addCallback("startExec", DojoExternalInterface, startExec);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		ExternalInterface.addCallback("setNumberArguments", DojoExternalInterface,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:																	setNumberArguments);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		ExternalInterface.addCallback("chunkArgumentData", DojoExternalInterface,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:																	chunkArgumentData);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		ExternalInterface.addCallback("exec", DojoExternalInterface, exec);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		ExternalInterface.addCallback("getReturnLength", DojoExternalInterface,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:																	getReturnLength);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		ExternalInterface.addCallback("chunkReturnData", DojoExternalInterface,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:																	chunkReturnData);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		ExternalInterface.addCallback("endExec", DojoExternalInterface, endExec);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// set whether communication is available

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	public static function chunkReturnData(segment:Number):String{
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var numSegments = DojoExternalInterface.getReturnLength();
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var startCut = segment * 1024;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var endCut = segment * 1024 + 1024;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		if(segment == (numSegments - 1)){
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:			endCut = segment * 1024 + DojoExternalInterface.resultData.length;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		}
