war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var piece = DojoExternalInterface.resultData.substring(startCut, endCut);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		//getURL("javascript:console.debug('FLASH: chunking return piece="+piece+"')");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		return piece;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	}

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	private static function decodeData(data):String{
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// we have to use custom encodings for certain characters when passing
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// them over; for example, passing a backslash over as //// from JavaScript
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// to Flash doesn't work
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, "&custom_backslash;", "\\");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, "\\\'", "\'");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, "\\\"", "\"");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		return data;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	private static function encodeData(data){
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		//getURL("javascript:console.debug('inside flash, data before="+data+"')");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// double encode all entity values, or they will be mis-decoded
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// by Flash when returned
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, "&", "&amp;");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// certain XMLish characters break Flash's wire serialization for
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// ExternalInterface; encode these into a custom encoding, rather than
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// the standard entity encoding, because otherwise we won't be able to
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// differentiate between our own encoding and any entity characters
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// that are being used in the string itself
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, '<', '&custom_lt;');
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, '>', '&custom_gt;');
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		// encode control characters and JavaScript delimiters
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, "\n", "\\n");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, "\r", "\\r");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, "\f", "\\f");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, "'", "\\'");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		data = DojoExternalInterface.replaceStr(data, '"', '\"');
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		//getURL("javascript:console.debug('inside flash, data after="+data+"')");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		return data;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	/** 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:			Flash ActionScript has no String.replace method or support for
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:			Regular Expressions! We roll our own very simple one.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	*/
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	private static function replaceStr(inputStr:String, replaceThis:String, 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:																		 withThis:String):String {
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		var splitStr = inputStr.split(replaceThis)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		inputStr = splitStr.join(withThis)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:		return inputStr;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/DojoExternalInterface.as:	private static function getDojoPath(){

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:/**
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: * Based on the expressinstall.as class created by Geoff Stearns as part
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: * of the FlashObject library.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: * Use this file to invoke the Macromedia Flash Player Express Install functionality
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: * This file is intended for use with the FlashObject embed script. You can download FlashObject 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: * and this file at the following URL: http://blog.deconcept.com/flashobject/
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: * Usage: 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *          var ExpressInstall = new ExpressInstall();
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *          
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *          // test to see if install is needed:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *          if (ExpressInstall.needsUpdate) { // returns true if update is needed
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *              ExpressInstall.init(); // starts the update
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *          }
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *	NOTE: Your Flash movie must be at least 214px by 137px in order to use ExpressInstall.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: *
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as: */
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:class ExpressInstall {
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	public var needsUpdate:Boolean;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	private var updater:MovieClip;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	private var hold:MovieClip;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	public function ExpressInstall(){
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:		// does the user need to update?
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:		this.needsUpdate = (_root.MMplayerType == undefined) ? false : true;	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	public function init():Void{
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:		this.loadUpdater();
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	}
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:	public function loadUpdater():Void {
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:		System.security.allowDomain("fpdownload.macromedia.com");
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:		// hope that nothing is at a depth of 10000000, you can change this depth if needed, but you want
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/flash/flash8/ExpressInstall.as:		// it to be on top of your content if you have any stuff on the first frame

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:Version 1.0.0

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:prototype / expermental 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:Credits
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	Peter Higgins (dante)

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:Project description
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	dojox.fx provides a class of animation effects to use, and
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	other animation addons to dojo base.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:Dependencies:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	dojox.fx requires dojo (core) and the dojo.fx package
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	dojox.fx.easing requires only dojo core. 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:Documentation
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	existing API surface: 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	dojox.fx._base:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	- dojox.fx.crossFade - crossfade two nodes easily
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	- dojox.fx.sizeTo - size a node about it's center to a new width/height
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	- dojox.fx.slideBy - slide a node by a t,l offset
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	- dojox.fx.highlight - animates the background color of a node, and returns
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:		it to the color it was. 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	(all use standard _Animation properties, like duration, easing, node, etc)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	dojox.fx._core:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	- dojox.fx._Line - a 2-d _Line implementation, backwards compatible with
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:		dojo._Line ... you might could safely do something akin to
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:		dojo._Line.prototype = dojox.fx._Line.prototype;
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:		and enable this for all dojo _Animations?
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	dojox.fx.style: - experimental CSS animation via class definitions
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	- dojox.fx.addClass - animate the effects of applying a class to a node
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	- dojox.fx.removeClass - "   "    "    "   removing a class from a node
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	- dojox.fx.toggleClass - wrapper for addClass/removeClass
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:	dojox.fx.easing: - a collection of easing functions to use
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:		this is a "stand alone" class, and can be used via:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:		dojo.require("dojox.fx.easing"); 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:		and provides: 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:			dojo.fx.easing.easeIn/easeOut/easeInOut
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:		to use in an _Animation easing: property	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/fx/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:Project description
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:Implementation of simple portable 2D graphics library.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:Dependencies:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:Dojo Core
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:Documentation
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:Currently it can be found here: http://docs.google.com/Doc?id=d764479_1hnb2tn
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:HTMLCanvas Renderer Status
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:To use canvas rendering, insert 'canvas' at the beginning of the gfxRenderers list in your
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:djConfig, for example:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:<script type="text/javascript" src="../../../dojo/dojo.js" 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	djConfig="parseOnLoad: true, gfxRenderer: 'canvas,svg,silverlight,vml'"></script>
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:canvas currently will only render on non-IE browsers (see dojox/gfx.js for where the renderer is loaded);
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:although it should be possible to use an IE canvas implementation (like Google's); however, it will be very slow.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:The following tests can be made to work with HTML Canvas with minor testcase modification:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:dojox/gfx/tests
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_gfx.html-Bugs #1
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_arc.html
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_bezier.html
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_pattern.html
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_gradient.html 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_linearGradient.html  
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_image1.html - Limitation #3 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_transform.html - Bug #1
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_poly.html - Bug #1
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:dojox/gfx/demos

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	test_chart2d.html - 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	// To make charts work, the following line needs to be added to the end of the 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	// Chart2D.js render() method (prior to return)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	if(this.surface.render){this.surface.render()};	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:Known Limitations:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:1) event handling- plan is to capture all events at canvas, perform intersect/hit 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   tests (not implemented) against scene graph, then propogate event to top-most 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   intersected shape.  HtmlCanvas shape need intersectsStroke and intersectsBounds, 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   and intersects (region).  
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:2) SVG and VML are "live" scene graphs; eg. any state change to objects in the 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   scene automatically get rendered in next engine render pass. For canvas, it's 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   procedural, and current implementation requires application to call surface.render() 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   whenever scene needs to be updated. Plan is to do dirty region checking based 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   on bounding boxes (currently not properly computed), and track dirty areas anytime 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   state changes (invalidate) separate from render phase.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   Add the following call where changes to the scene graph are complete and you want to
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   render:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	if (surface.render){surface.render();} 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:4) Text/Text Paths - Text shape is implemented using DIV overlays.  Many text styles are not
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   applied, and outline/fills are not possible.  This is due to limitations in Canvas spec.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   Firefox 3.0 has proprietary text functions that we could test for and use once FF3 is out.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   No luck on Safari.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:3) No Image skewing - Limitation of Canvas 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:	
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:Known Bugs:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:1) Matrix xformations (applied from root to shape leaf nodes) not quite right--but very close.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   Canvas does not have a built in transformation function that allows skewing.  Need to 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   track skew matrix with Shape, and perform other trans/rot/scale transformations without 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:   using canvas transform functions.  
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/gfx/README:

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:Project description 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	A class to provide a common API for images, and home for image
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	related Widgets.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README: 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:Dependencies:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	LightBox: dojo core, dojox.fx and optionally dojox.data. uses
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	either tundra or soria theme, no standalone icons.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	SlideShow: dojo core, dojo.fx, and dojo.data (optional 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	dojox.data store implementations apply)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	ThumbNailPicker: dojo core, dojo.fx and dojo.data. Combined
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	with a SlideShow, creates a sample Gallery app.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	Gallery: core, dojox.image.SlideShow, dojox.image.ThumbNailPicker
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	LightBox: currently works as individual items, and grouped items,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	but usage of dojo.data is broken (atm). the API is subject to 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README: 	change, and is marked accordingly.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	a common API provided by dojox.image.Pane (?)

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	SlideShow: Shows an image, one by one, from a datastore. Acts
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	as standing ImagePane implementation, 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	Gallery: A combination Thumbnail view and SlideShow, using
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/image/README:	a datastore, and providing navigation, and common API.

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:Credits
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:	James Burke (jburke@dojotoolkit.org)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:Project description
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:The XHR IFrame Proxy (xip) allows you to do cross-domain XMLHttpRequests (XHRs).
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:It works by using two iframes, one your domain (xip_client.html), one on the 
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:other domain (xip_server.html). They use fragment IDs in the iframe URLs to pass
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:messages to each other. The xip.js file defines dojox.io.proxy.xip. This module
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:intercepts XHR calls made by the Dojo XHR methods (dojo.xhr* methods). The module
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:returns a facade object that acts like an XHR object. Once send is called on the
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:facade, the facade's data is serialized, given to xip_client.html. xip_client.html
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:then passes the serialized data to xip_server.html by changing xip_server.html's
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:URL fragment ID (the #xxxx part of an URL). xip_server.html deserializes the
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:message fragments, and does an XHR call, gets the response, and serializes the
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:data. The serialized data is then passed back to xip_client.html by changing
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:xip_client.html's fragment ID. Then the response is deserialized and used as
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:the response inside the facade XHR object that was created by dojox.io.proxy.xip.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:Dependencies:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:xip.js: Dojo Core, dojox.data.dom
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:xip_client.html: none
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:xip_server.html: none (but see Additional Notes section)
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:Documentation
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:There is some documentation that applies to the Dojo 0.4.x version of these files:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:http://dojotoolkit.org/book/dojo-book-0-4/part-5-connecting-pieces/i-o/cross-domain-xmlhttprequest-using-iframe-proxy
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:The general theory still applies to this code, but the specifics are different
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:for the Dojo 0.9+ codebase. Doc updates hopefully after the basic code is ported.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:The current implementation destroys the iframes used for a request after the request
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:completes. This seems to cause a memory leak, particularly in IE. So, it is not
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:suited for doing polling cross-domain requests.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:Installation instructions
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:

war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:http://svn.dojotoolkit.org/var/src/dojo/dojox/trunk/io/proxy/xip.js
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:http://svn.dojotoolkit.org/var/src/dojo/dojox/trunk/io/proxy/xip_client.html
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:Install into the following directory structure:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:/dojox/io/proxy/
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:...which should be at the same level as your Dojo checkout.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:Grab the following from the Dojox SVN Repository:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:http://svn.dojotoolkit.org/var/src/dojo/dojox/trunk/io/proxy/xip_server.html
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:and install it on the domain that you want to allow receiving cross-domain
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:requests. Be sure to read the documentation, the Additional Notes below, and
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:the in-file comments.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:Additional Notes
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:xip_client.html and xip_server.html do not work right away. You need to uncomment
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:out the script tags in the files. Additionally, xip_server.html requires a JS file,
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:isAllowed.js, to be defined. See the notes in xip_server.html for more informaiton.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:XDOMAIN BUILD INSTRUCTIONS:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:The dojox.io.proxy module requires some setup to use with an xdomain build.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:The xip_client.html file has to be served from the same domain as your web page.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:It cannot be served from the domain that has the xdomain build. Download xip_client.html
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:and install it on your server. Then set djConfig.xipClientUrl to the local path
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:of xip_client.html (just use a path, not a whole URL, since it will be on the same
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:domain as the page). The path to the file should be the path relative to the web
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:page that is using dojox.io.proxy.
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
war/src/main/webapp/javascript/dojox/io/proxy/README:
